        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Odonto-onycho dysplasia-alopecia syndrome is a rare genetic ectodermal dysplasia syndrome characterized by almost total alopecia with only sparse thin brittle slow-growing scalp hair fair and sparse eyebrows and eyelashes absent axillary and pubic hair fragile and brittle fingernails thick and brittle toenails (both with a subungual corneal layer) hypodontia microdontia widely spaced teeth with hypoplastic enamel mild palmoplantar keratosis caf√©-au-lait spots and areolae anomalies. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1985."
        },
